
<p>Directory stacks are handy to get back to a previous directory. You
can manipulate the stack with push and popd. The command pushd is a
bit long for me so I use the option auto_pushd instead.</p>

<pre class="src">
<span style="color: #008b00; background-color: #b9babd;"># </span><span style="color: #008b00; background-color: #b9babd;">automatically do a pushd of each cd in a directory
</span><span style="color: #00688b; background-color: #b9babd;">setopt</span> auto_pushd
</pre>

<p>Now the directories are inserted in the stack with each cd command.</p>

<p>There is a neat way to switch to any directory in the stack by using
completion.</p>

<pre class="example">
     cd - TAB
0 -- /home/ivan
1 -- /home/ivan/www/english
2 -- /home/ivan/keep
</pre>

<p>Hitting the TAB key shows you the entire stack. Just input the number
and it will switch to that directory.</p>

